  "summary": "Data without context rarely creates usable intelligence.",
  "body": "Joz believes intelligence emerges from context rather than isolated data.\n\nA metric, document, report, or model output only becomes meaningful when connected to:\n\n- purpose\n- history\n- ownership\n- constraints\n- confidence\n- business impact\n\nThis principle directly influences his work in RAG, context engineering, memory systems, and enterprise knowledge architectures.\n\nContext creates understanding.\nUnderstanding creates better decisions.",
